<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="galactosidase_gal">Galactosidase (GAL)</a> - Part of an <a href="#assay">assay</a> frequently used in genetics, molecular biology, and other life sciences. An active <a href="#enzyme">enzyme</a> may be detected using <a href="#x_gal">X-Gal,</a> which forms an intense blue product after <a href="#cleavage">cleavage</a> by <a href="#β_galactosidase_lactase_β_gal_beta_gal">β-Galactosidase</a>, and is easy to identify and quantify.